INSERT INTO `devtasdetails` (`id`, `name`, `description`, `sloka`, `image`, `points`, `otherDetails`) VALUES
(1, 'ROGA', '{\"p1\":\"Mrityu was born off the wedlock of Bhaya and Maya who belonged to the Dharma clan which emerged out of Prajapati Daksha Mrityu has five sons - Vyadhi, Jara, Shoka, Trishna and Krodha. Vyadhi is synonymous with Roga and occupies the north west pada in the Vaastu chakra. He is the most frightful of the Gods and grants death and bondage Angering him results in death.\"}', 'ॐ शिरोमेश्रीर्यशोमुखंत्विषिः केशाश्चश्मश्रूणि राजामेप्राणोऽअमृतं सम्राट् चक्षुर्विराटश्रोत्रम्।। ॐभू भो रोग इहा रोगाय नमः।।', 'assets/devtas/RogaN1.jpg', '{\"1\":\"Drainer of energies, Fever.\",\"2\":\"It gives sickness, disease and weakness.\",\"3\":\"If it\'s weak, our body is weak to face challenges.\",\"4\":\"State: Beta (Pranmaya), Due to Roga (disease), Physical as well as Energy Body get weakened, vitality & Energy in the body is adversely affected\",\"5\":\"Chakra: Manipur (2.4)\",\"6\":\"During disease, doctors recommend light food, Manipura rules digestion, it is also affected by Roga and get weakned.\",\"7\":\"If balanced, it destroys diseases and provides energy, gives abilities to deal with tough times.\",\"8\":\"Death like pain if entrance here.\",\"9\":\"Mirrors placed here, person expands his horizon of support to his relatives and friends and expects same from them.\",\"10\":\"Sitting here when balanced, person received support from all walks of life.\",\"11\":\"If balanced, makes a person energetic and supportive\",\"12\":\"Toilet – fails to receive company or adequate support from family\",\"13\":\"Mother of the family is more disturbed if imbalanced\",\"14\":\"Grey Stones or their photos in this energy field give a lot of stability after balancing.\",\"15\":\"If you want someone\'s support, by placing the photo of boss with him in happy times is good.\",\"16\":\"If someone claims – “boss is not supporting, keep his own photo with boss here”\"}', '{\"name\":\"ROGA (N1)\",\"color\":\"blue\",\"direction\":\"NW\",\"C1\":\"Drainer/Weakner\",\"C2\":\"Left hand/Banya agrabhuj\",\"C3\":\"Pranamaya Kosha\",\"C4\":\"Swadhisthan/Beta\",\"C5\":\"Pearl\"}'),
(2, 'Bhallat', '{\"p1\":\" The Vasu named Prabhas, who is the father of Vishwakarma, has found a place close to Vishwakarma in the Vaastu chakra. Samrangan Sutradhar has considered Bhallata to be the Moon, but when the question of installing the eight vasus in the vaastu chakra arises, they have mostly been assigned places in the north. The father son or associate duo of Indra-Jayant, Aap-Aapvatsa, Savitra-Savita have found adjacent places. In the same order, Prabhasvasu has been placed next to Vishwakarma. If a door is located in this place, then a lot of wealth enters the house.\"}', 'ॐबण्महाँ 2।। असि सूर्य बळादित्यमहाँ 2असि।। महते सतो महिमापनस्यतेद्धादेव महाँ 2।। असि।। ॐ भूर्भुवः स्वर्भोभल्लाटइहा भल्लाटायनमः।।', 'assets/devtas/Bhallat N4.jpg', '{\"1\":\"Helps to achieve something big, it\'s the power to give colossal abundance. It is it’s power which magnifies our efforts and also the results of those efforts and, makes them very big.\",\"2\":\"Abundance, Expansion, super natural being, Yeti.\",\"3\":\"When we try to achieve something big in any domain of our life, then, the power of Bhallat works in conjunction with the power of Bhudhar to manifest our desire and to make our efforts successful.\",\"4\":\"Caretaker of wealth of Kuber.\",\"5\":\"It possesses the quality of brave, wise and ethical character.\",\"6\":\"Entrance here brings abundance of inherited and earned money/It gives you those skills, with which you can increase your work or assets in manifold/ male dominated family/ people want to do big in execution.\",\"7\":\"Imbalance – Gives problem with father and less or no money from father.\",\"8\":\"It gives you that kind of thoughts to do things on big scale.\",\"9\":\"Keep a money plant with big leaves to attract growth opportunities in our life.\",\"10\":\"A living room or bed room here people are able to dream big.\",\"11\":\"Toilet here discourages people to expand their work.\"}', '{\"name\":\"Bhallata(N4)\",\"color\":\"Yellow\",\"direction\":\"North \",\"C1\":\"Expansion/Abundance creator\",\"C2\":\"Vigyanmaya Kosha \",\"C3\":\"Left Back/Banya Pasharva\",\"C4\":\" Agya/Theta \"}'),
(3, 'Bhujang', '{\"p1\":\"Bhujanga or Sarpa refers to the malefic serpent deity. This is a name for Ahi or Vritra, the Vedic demon of drought, who coils himself around the cloud mountains and holds the water in the clouds, stopping them from raining on the earth. Indra then uses his thunderbolt or Vajra to free the waters. Vritra was created by a sage named Tvashtri in order to defeat Indra who however succeeded in bringing about the end of Vritra. Sarpas have emerged from the womb of Kadru, the daughter of Prajapati Daksha and they started living on earth. Indra resided on the bed of Sheshnaga and Lord Krishna danced on the Kaliya Naga. Sarpa has also been called Kaala, son of Dhruva and granson of Dharmaraj and Vasu.\",\"p2\":\"Sarpas have been called the semi divine community like the Gandharvas and they reside on the earth, in the universe and in the infernal region. They were referred to as Gods in the Atharva Veda. This god has been assigned the pada in the north, towards the north east and on the left shoulder of the Vaastu purush.\"}', 'ॐ उदुत्यंजातवेदसंदेवंवहंतिकेतवः दृशेविश्वाय सूर्य स्वाहा।।', 'assets/devtas/Bhujang N6.jpg', '{\"1\":\"In Atharva Ved, it is Asur Anant Naga. Even Gods get scare. He is the one who evoked as the protector of treasure of life; health.\",\"2\":\"If imbalance, the person is very rude and talks very ill. Can disregard anyone\",\"3\":\"Protector of life saving medicines, herbs and treasures under earth.\",\"4\":\"Mind is restless an  easily irritable\",\"5\":\"Toilet here can give cancer\",\"6\":\"Entrance here, residents exhibit fanatic kind of behaviour/enmity from progeny and stress\",\"7\":\"Dustbin will cause irritation in throat\",\"8\":\"Heavy goods will cause problem in lower Jaw\",\"9\":\"Drinking water storage will cause continuous cold and cough here\",\"10\":\"Kitchen is worst here\",\"11\":\"Store will only give diseases\",\"12\":\"Seepage, fungus, toilet, nala can give throat related issues\",\"13\":\"When the power of Bhujag is in balance in the building, it ensures health and smooth flow of money is maintained.\",\"14\":\"Main deity for sexuality. In yoga and Tantra tradition, i is connected with kundalini power.\"}', '{\"name\":\"BHUJAG (N6)\",\"color\":\"Yellow\",\"direction\":\"NNE \",\"C1\":\"Core Strength/Immunity\",\"C2\":\" Manomaya Kosha\",\"C3\":\"Left Chest/Banyi Chhati \",\"C4\":\"Sahastrar/Delta\"}'),
(4, 'Mukhya', '{\"p1\":\" Vishwakarma or Tvashta has been considered as the Mukhya god. He is the son of Prabhas Vasu, one of the Ashta vasus, who was married to Jupiter\'s sister. Tvashta is counted among the twelve Adityas and Godmother Aditi is his mother.\",\"p2\":\" Tvashta also refers to the Sun, as he lives in all corporal forms. As Tvashta, he made Indra\'s vajra, with the help of which he killed the powerful serpent Vritra. He is the Vedic vulcan, the shaper, craftsman. The Sun is the maker of the day. He is the radiant one. He is one of the most important of the celestial Vedic gods who is the source of life and healing. As the giver of food, sight, health, knowledge and intelligence, he is the greatest of the Adityas.\",\"p3\":\" He rules the pada in the north direction, near the left elbow of the Vaastu purush. Vishwakarma is the father of Vaastu shastra and his son was skilled in the Sthapatya kalaa, which over a period of time got diversified in the form of carpenters, goldsmiths, ironmongers etc. He is worshipped so as to ensure that the construction is vaastu compatible and completed without any obstacles arising.\"}', 'ॐइषेत्वोर्जेत्वा वायवस्थदेवोवः सविता प्रार्थयतु श्रेठतमायकर्मणऽ आप्यायध्वमन्ध्याऽइन्द्रायभागम्प्रजावतीरनमीवा अयमामावस्तेनईशतमाघ शर्छ सोध्रुवाअस्मिन् गोपतौस्यातबहीर्यजमानस्य पशून्पाहि। ॐ भूर्भुवः स्वर्भोमुख्य इहा मुख्यायनमः।।', 'assets/devtas/mukhya.jpg', '{\"1\":\"If zone is well organised, the house will be well organised\",\"2\":\"In certain vastu books, it is associated with Vishwakarma, he has four children.\",\"3\":\"Entrance here gives lots of money, male off springs/ Overall bliss/make people very manageable with task given to them, done in a way that everybody benefits/sense of organisation and sense of allocation of task comes from entrance here.\",\"4\":\"It is predominantly a male energy field\",\"5\":\"If it\'s balanced, and a person sleeps here, makes a person very meticulous, systematic.\",\"6\":\"If the mother or mother