(9, 'SHIKHI', '{\"p1\":\"Shikhi rules the first cell of the Ekasheetipada from the north east direction. The word Shikhi is symbolic of a peak and means fire or peacock. The qualities of Shikhi are like that of Agni. Shikhi rules the head of the Vaastu purush.\",\"p2\":\"The reference to his birth is found in the Padma Purana. Anala is a synonym of Shikhi. Anala is one of the Ashtavasus. Vasu, the daughter of Daksh and wife of Dharma, was the mother of Anala. The Vaastu purush is full of energy and is fiery in nature and Shikhi has found a place in his head. All the sons of Anala have the qualities of fire and in some places Anala has been considered as the reincarnation of Lord Agni.\"}', 'ॐतमीशानंलगतस्तस्थुषस्पतिं धियजिन्वमवसेहूमहेवयम्। पूषानोयथावेदसामसद्वृधेरक्षितापायुरदब्धः स्वस्तये।।ॐ भूर्भुवः स्वः भो: शिखिन् इहागच्छ इहातिष्ठ ॐशिखिने नमः शिखिनमावाहयामि इतिस्थापनम्।।1।।', 'assets/devtas/Shikhi E1.jpg', '{\"1\":\"Third eye of Shiva\",\"2\":\"Ideas, Right Brain, CNS, Eyes, Peace, Giver, Serenity (Shaant chita)\",\"3\":\"Power to conceive any idea and condense them\",\"4\":\"Need to check this devta when we find ourselves at loss of ideas\",\"5\":\"Heavy stuff kept here can also cause imbalance\",\"6\":\"Imbalances here causes issues of eyesight\",\"7\":\"Office gate here will cause problems related to electricity\",\"8\":\"Entrance here gives fire,  accidents and losses/Brings sorrow, loss and proneness to fire outbreak\",\"9\":\"Kitchen here causes anger and frustration, lots of mental disturbance.\",\"10\":\"A store over here causes blocked mind set.\",\"11\":\"A toilet here can be associated with mental defects.\",\"12\":\"Sitting here for long gives disinterest in life, for some time it is good.\",\"13\":\"As per traditional vastu, put water in household here\",\"14\":\"Water symbolizes ideas, o bring new ideas we put water in shikhi\",\"15\":\"A bedroom over here doesn\'t provide good sleep, constant anxiety and thinking.\"}', '{\"name\":\"Shikhi  (E1)\",\"co