(10, 'Rudra', '{\"p1\":\"In the Vedas, Rudra is the god of storms and the howling terrible God. He is a destructive deity who brings diseases upon men and cattle on one hand and is a beneficient deity with a healing influence on the other. In the Puranas it is stated that Brahma desired to create a son and Rudra came into existence as a youth. He wept and asked for a name and was given the name of Rudra. He is the personification of the uncultured force, causing destruction and disarray.\",\"p2\":\"The eleven rudras according to Mahabharat are Manyu, Manu, Mahinash, Mahaan, Shiva, Rijadhwaja, Ugrareta, Bhav, Kaala, Vaamdeva, Dhritvrita. Rudra is more often synonymous with Shiva. Shiva is the third of the Hindu triad of Brahma, Vishnu and Mahesh. He is said to have emerged from the frown of Vishnu, wielding a trident in order to protect Brahma from the demons. Thus Shiva manifested himself as the destroyer and that is the attribute always attached to him. Since all things are subject to decay and destruction, it was necessary to have the destroyer or indirectly the recreator allowing all forms of creation to manifest again. Death is not death but simply a manifestation into a new life.\",\"p3\":\"In the Vaastu chakra, Rudra is positioned on the diagonal line connecting the Brahma kendra padas with the north west corner.\"}', 'ॐसुमाणपृथिवींद्यामनेहसठ सुशर्माणमदितिर्छ सुप्रणीतिम्। दवींनावठ स्वरित्रामनागसमस्रवन्तीमा रुहेसास्वस्तये।। ॐ भू भोरुद्रइहा रुद्रायनमः।।', 'assets/devtas/Rudra W7W8.jpg', '{\"1\":\"Channelizing support\",\"2\":\"The fierce God, untamed one, Shiva, wind and storm, multi form, strong, God of untamed, Forest\",\"3\":\"Described as cunning and head of thieves.\",\"4\":\"He has a special methodology for treatment and cure.\",\"5\":\"The power which makes water streams flow on earth has also been termed as Rudra.\",\"6\":\"Shiva form, responsible for all types of flow of activities, Flow of emotions, flow of tears starts from Rudra and stops at Shosha.\",\"7\":\"Sustaining day to day activities without interruption\",\"8\":\"Emotional imbalance\",\"9\":\"It also ensures flow of ideas, a support system\",\"10\":\"Ability to complete work with ease\",\"11\":\"It is advised to make grainery here as ht grains in form of food keeps the flow of life.\",\"12\":\"In factories, the consumption of finished goods keeps the company flowing, so it is a good place to keep finished goods.\",\"13\":\"The power which generate tears is Rudra\",\"14\":\"Air is its essence, heavily influenced by the moon; this is rulers of mind and emotions.\"}', '{\"name\":\"Rudra (N7)\",\"color\":\"blue\",\"direction\":\"NW1 \",\"C1\":\"Clearing/Channelizer\",\"C2\":\"Manomaya Kosha\",\"C3\":\"Finger of left hand/ \",\"C4\":\"Banyi Hatheli ki ungli  \",\"C5\":\"Vishuddhi/Beta\",\"C6\":\"Pearl\"}'),
