illness and bad returns which are called Paapyakshma.\"}', '{\"name\":\"PAPAYAKSHMA (N8)\",\"color\":\"Green\",\"direction\":\"NW \",\"C1\":\"Addictive/Addictor \",\"C2\":\"Pranmaya Kosha\",\"C3\":\"Left elbow/Banyi kohni\",\"C4\":\"Manipur/Beta\"}'),
(12, 'Parjanya', '{\"p1\":\"Parjanya rules the second cell of the Ekasheetipada from the north east direction. He was one of the twelve adityas. According to the Vishnu Purana, he is the guardian of the month of Kartika, a Gandharva and a Rishi in the Harivamsa. He is also counted amidst the 33 gods described in the Vedas. His parents were Sage Kashyap and Aditi. He rules the right eye of the Vaastu Purush. He is the lord of the rain water and is responsible for the rains. According to the Rig Veda, the clouds are called Parjanya. His main weapon is the lightening produced by clouds. Parjanya protects the earth with his water and makes it fertile to produce plants and trees\",\"p2\":\"Parjanya not only has the ability to bring about rainfall, but also has the ability to stop the rains in case of floods and heavy downpours. On one side he is related to Indra because of the rains, and on the other side, he is related to Sun on account of the lightening. Parjanya represents the electrical energy brought to earth by the rain, rejuvenating it and making it fertile. He is sometimes seen as a fertility god.\",\"p3\":\"It has been mentioned in the Atharva Veda that Earth is the mother and Parjanya is the father. Parjanya is known for bestowing female children and for enhancing the capabilities of women.\"}', 'ॐमहारऽएइंद्रोवज्रहस्त: षोडशीशर्मयच्छतु हन्तुपाप्मानयोस्मान्वेष्टि। । उप यामगृहीतोसिमहेंद्रायत्वैषतेयोनिर्महेंद्रायत्वा। ॐ भूर्भुवः स्वः भोः पर्जन्यइहागच्छइहतिष्ठ।', 'assets/devtas/Prajanya E2.jpg', '{\"1\":\"Best place to meditate, gives shower of insights, it helps us evolve\",\"2\":\"Refreshment, Insights, Fertile Thoughts, & Fertility in women, Evolving\",\"3\":\"Associated with Flora and Fauna\",\"4\":\"It is responsible for growth in plants and production of fruits.\",\"5\":\"It is invokes in Vedas as the power of fertility in women and cows.\",\"6\":\"Entrance here gives more female birth, wasteful expenditure/drain of wealth and bereavement.\",\"7\":\"If the door placed here power of Pingla Nadi drains away, masculine power of place drains, so more girls born.\",\"8\":\"Theta+Agya+Vigyanmaya gives insight, intuition, sanskara.\",\"9\":\"Effects more females than males.\",\"10\":\"However the females belong to this place are very bold and take care of their family like a son.\",\"11\":\"Lot of efforts without any result if toilet here.\",\"12\":\"Related to women Fertility issues if imbalance\",\"13\":\"Washing machine here – females cannot conceive\",\"14\":\"Dustbin can cause ovarian cyst.\",\"15\":\"No adequate returns if kitchen here\",\"16\":\"Bedroom ensures very good sleep\",\"17\":\"Mother child photo improves their relationship, their bonding\",\"18\":\"Flower bucket after balancing shows better results in returns.\",\"19\":\"Fruit basket creates abundance\",\"20\":\"Entrance here gives more girls born/wasteful expenditure\"}', '{\"name\":\"PARJANYA  (E2)\",\"color\":\"\",\"direction\":\"ENE\",\"C1\":\"Evolving/Insights giver\",\"C2\":\"Vigyanmaya Kosh\",\"C3\":\"Right Eye/Dahina Netra\",\"C4\":\"Agya/Theta\"}'),
(13, 'Shosha', '{\"p1\":\"Shosha is considered to be the God of mourning and if this god is annoyed he brings reason to mourn. If a sorrowful person stays in this part, he tends to feel light because his tears start falling on their own. The Samrangan Sutradhar considers Shosha to be Saturn, the son of the Sun. Shosh is said to be imbibed with the qualities of Saturn. If a door is constructed here, then there is loss and destruction of wealth. Shosh is also synonymous with shoka meaning mourning. In the Vaastu chakra he is placed next to Asura.\"}', 'ॐअसवेस्वाहा सववेस्वाहा विश्वेभ्यः स्वाहा विवस्वते स्वाहा गणश्रियेस्वाहा गणपतयेस्वाहाभिभुवेस्वाहाधिपतये स्वाहाशूषायस्वाहा सर्छ सायस्वाहा चंद्रायस्वाहा ज्योतिषस्वाहा मलिम्लुचायस्वाहादिवापतयेतेस्वाहा।। ॐॐभू भोः शोक इहा ॐशोकायनमः।', 'assets/devtas/Sosha W7.jpg', '{\"1\":\"When the residents feel low due to negative experiences and emotionally and mentally breakdown, it helps relaxing and detoxifying.\",\"2\":\"It is meant to dry up things. Where tears dry.\",\"3\":\"This is the ability to communicate our thoughts and share our feelings and clear our hearts to feel light.\",\"4\":\"Effect of planet Shani can be parallel to this energy field.\",\"5\":\"Thyroid problem occurs when we are not able to communicate our feelings (vishuddhi chakra), if this zone is either cut or extended.\",\"6\":\"Cut cause depression in life/relations become tense, because they can\'t share well.\",\"7\":\"I extended, we can\'t stop crying, living in past miseries.\",\"8\":\"A bed here makes you depress although spending some time here is good.\",\"9\":\"Shoe-rack and dustbin can be kept here.\",\"10\":\"If past thoughts are still troubling you, giving you depression, this field is disturbed.\",\"11\":\"Entrance here gives drug addiction due to loss of happiness/loss of wealth and brings stress.\"}', '{\"name\":\"shosha  (w7)\",\"color\":\"Yellow\",\"direction\":\"WNW\",\"C1\":\"Transparency/Dryer\",\"C2\":\"Pranamaya Kosha\",\"C3\":\"Left Back/Banya Pasharva\",\"C4\":\"Vishuddhi/Alpha\"}'),
(14, 'Rajyakshama', '{\"p1\":\"Rajyakshama is the fierce form of Rudra. He is related to the diseases of the lungs. Rudra moves through the medium of air and exists in the air. Rajyakshama spreads in the body through the air and makes the body diseased. The body becomes stagnant.\",\"p2\":\"Rajyakshama occupies a very significant place in the Vaastu chakra. He is placed on the pada that is triangular to Brahma, Prithvidhara and Mitra.\"}', 'ॐअभिगोत्राणि सहसागाहमानोदयो वीरः शतमन्युरिन्द्रः। दुश्च्यवनः पृतनाषाडयुध्योस्माकं सेनाऽअवतुप्रयुत्सु।। ॐभू भोराजयक्ष्मनिहा राजयक्ष्मणेनमः।।', 'assets/devtas/Rajyakshma N1N2.jpg', '{\"1\":\"The Holder\",\"2\":\"Attendant of Rudra\",\"3\":\"Lord of all roots, keep the root and strengthen it.\",\"4\":\"Kosha: Rajyakshama has influence over Manomaya Kosha, mind is concentrated at whatever is created by Brahama\",\"5\":\"State: Beta depicting Anamaya Kosha\",\"6\":\"Since the foetus has to develop physically and the development of physical body takes place inside the mother womb, the Kosha should be Anamaya\",\"7\":\"Chakra: Muladhar (for Birth Process, Muladhara is the chakra to make this happen)\",\"8\":\"It also stills the mind. If energy of this zone becomes imbalanced (kupita), then due to air being wrathful the mind becomes very much unstable.\",\"9\":\"It helps to stop the idea in the mind for further implementation\",\"10\":\"If imbalanced, support will come but will not last\",\"11\":\"Rudra is like water, Rajyakshma is like dam, both are necessary.\",\"12\":\"Rudra ensure it is coming, Rajyakshma ensures to keep it and make it profitable for you.\",\"13\":\"This energy ceases universal mind for a moment so that the creation of life could initiate. Unless that cessation happens, creation is not possible.\",\"14\":\"It is the power to hold that cessation and the new walls around that space in which the life manifests and which in turn, initiates the creation of the whole world.\"}', '{\"name\":\"Rajyakshama \",\"color\":\"Blue\",\"direction\":\"NW2\",\"C1\":\"Blocking/Holder\",\"C2\":\"Annamaya Kosha\",\"C3\":\"Left Palm/Banyi Hatheli\",\"C4\":\"Muladhar/Beta\",\"C5\":\"Pearl\"}'),
(15, 'AAPAHA', '{\"p1\":\"When we move from the Kendra padas of Brahma and move towards the north east corner, then we come across the pada for the God called Aap. There are four references to this god in the Rig Veda. She refers to mothers, young females, boon granting and Yajna blessing devis. They do not go against the laws set by Indra. They also follow the rules set by Savita. Aap is present wherever Mitra and Varuna meet.\",\"p2\":\"In the form of a mother, Aap creates fire. Aap is also associated with honey. When ghee (clarified butter) is added to honey, it becomes a drink fit for Indra. The association of mother, water, ghee and honey makes this pada very cool. At times the water in the earth is also associated with Aap.\"}', 'ॐआपोअस्मान्मातरः शुन्धयन्तुघृतेननोघृतवः पुनंतु। विश्वं हिरिप्रवहतिदेवीरुदिदाभ्यः शुचिरापूतऽएमि। ॐ भूर्भुवः स्वर्भो आप इहागच्छत। अभ्द्योनमः।।', 'assets/devtas/Aap N7N8.jpg', '{\"1\":\"Associated with healing, set to destroy ailments, gives healing powers\",\"2\":\"Ailments means challenges also, helps us to come out of these problems, gives healing.\",\"3\":\"If imbalance, it will destroy the healing power\",\"4\":\"Ability of the mind to face the challenges and overcome it\",\"5\":\"When balanced, we feel a kind of bliss, our intuitions are improved.\",\"6\":\"It referred as Himalayas. It flows all prana, life force, in forms of rivers and gives us all the ideas and healing powers to face the physical and mental challenges.\",\"7\":\"It has the power to free you from the fear.\",\"8\":\"It strengthen the immune system, it cures diseases and get long life.\",\"9\":\"It creates the vision and brings the driving force in humans. He is the life (prana) of all the water streams on the planet and is the causing factor of their movement.\"}', '{\"name\":\"AAPA\",\"color\":\"Red\",\"direction\":\"NE1\",\"C1\":\"Realization/Power of Manifestation\",\"C2\":\"Vigyanmya Kosha\",\"C3\":\"Mouth/Mukh\",\"C4\":\"Agya/Theta\",\"C5\":\"Pukhraj/Cat’s Eye\"}'),
(16, 'Jayant', '{\"p1\":\"Jayant is the son of Indra and Shuchi, daughter of the demon king Puloma. So Jayant is considered to have demonic qualities. Jayant is appeased through prayers inviting the vanquisher of enemies, and the one who is victorious over all the directions. Jayant rules the right ear of the Vaastu Purush. If there is a door in this position, then Jayant bestows unlimited wealth to the owner, confers fame and he establishes a monopoly in his sphere of work. Jayant rules the cell adjacent to Indra and it is assumed that the owner of the house can be a royal person or be related to a royal\"}', 'ॐधन्वनागा धन्वनाजिंजयेमधन्वनातीव्राः समदो जयेम। धनुः शत्रोरपकामं कृणोतिधन्वनासर्वाः प्रदिशोजयेम। ॐ भूर्भुवः स्वः भोः जयन्त इहागच्छ इह।।', 'assets/devtas/Jayanth E3.jpg', '{\"1\":\"It ensures that you are successful in all your undertakings.\",\"2\":\"The sense of being victorious comes from this energy field\",\"3\":\"Responsible for Zeal and enthusiasm\",\"4\":\"When we are too simplistic and not able to socialize due to complexities of strategies, we need to check this field\",\"5\":\"Sword to be put here.\",\"6\":\"Bedroom makes a person street smart\",\"7\":\"Toilet here gives negative effect in children, will not be able to express, very simplistic, shy.\",\"8\":\"Black colour or circular shape gives negative effects. Black is Saturn, sun and Saturn are enemy, so black colour is not good in field of sun.\",\"9\":\"Wine storage or book store will gives benefits in terms of social mingling.\",\"10\":\"Plants are very good here\",\"11\":\"It teaches Sam Daam Danda Bheda\",\"12\":\"Entrance here equipped the residents with everything that helps them enjoy success in the materialistic world/money, profits and success/brings wealth\",\"13\":\"Living room and dining are good here.\",\"14\":\"Manomaya---mind\",\"15\":\"Alpha -----creative solution\",\"16\":\"Manipur----action, determination\"}', '{\"name\":\"JAYANT (E3)\",\"color\":\"\",\"direction\":\"ENE\",\"C1\":\"Courage/Success maker\",\"C2\":\"Manomaya Kosh\",\"C3\":\"Right Ear/Dahina Kaan\",\"C4\":\"Manipur/Alpha\",\"C5\":\"Ruby\"}'),
(17, 'Bhudhar', '{\"p1\":\"Lord Vishnu is often depicted reclining on a coiled and many-headed cobra called Shesha Naga, which rests on the cosmic waters with his consort serving him at his feet. Prithvidhar is synonymous with Shesha naga. He is one of the Ashtavasus. Vasu, daughter of Prajapati Daksha and wife of Dharma, gave birth to a vasu named Dhar. Dhar came to be known as Prithvidhar with all the other vasus.\",\"p2\":\"In the Vastu mandal, Prithvidhar occupies the three padas lying to the north of Lord Brahma\'s padas.\"}', 'ॐपृथिवीछन्द : अन्तरिक्षंछन्द: द्यौश्छंद: समाश्छंद: नक्षत्राणिच्छंद: वाक्छंद: मनश्छंद: कृषिश्छंद : हिरण्यंछन्द: गौश्छन्द : अजा छन्दः अश्वश्छन्दः। ॐभू भो पृथ्वीधरइहा ॐपृथ्वीधरायनमः।।', 'assets/devtas/PRITVIDHAR or BHUDHAR N1 N8.jpg', '{\"1\":\"Holder of the earth\",\"2\":\"Which makes all the manifestation possible in to the existence?\",\"3\":\"Bhudhar ensures that nine months after seeding, it will protect the child metaphorically.\",\"4\":\"\'Bhu\' means -- to happen, to exist, to manifest; and \'dhar\' means the one who carries or contain it. So this field of energy is --\'the one who carries the power of manifestation.\'\",\"5\":\"Direction (N1 & N2) falling in [NW, NNW]\",\"6\":\"Bhudhar has Alpha State (Concentration, Single Minded, State of Absorption, No Duality) and it represents Manomaya Kosha which corresponds to Alpha Brainwave frequency\",\"7\":\"Whatever is created by The Brahama has to carried & manifested by Bhudhar so it has to be in Alpha State to help the development of foetus\",\"8\":\"Example: when a lady conceives, she has to carry the foetus for 9 months, during the 9 months she is different lady, watchful, careful in her eating, walking and activities\"}', '{\"name\":\"Bhudhar\",\"color\":\"Blue\",\"direction\":\"North\",\"C1\":\"Realization/Power of Manifestation\",\"C2\":\"Manomaya Kosha\",\"C3\":\"Left Chest/Banya Stan\",\"C4\":\"Swathisthan/Alpha\",\"C5\":\"Panna/Mercury\"}'),
(18, 'Asur', '{\"p1\":\"Asura refers to the malefic demons or the enemies of God indulging in violent and evil practices and activities. They are said to have been created by Prajapati Kashyap with the lower breath. Vedic history cites innumerous instances where gods and good mortals have been tormented by the demons and in some cases, god has incarnated himself in some or the other form to destroy these demonic creatures.\",\"p2\":\"When we move from west towards north west in the Vaastu chakra, Asura occupies the left armpit of the Vaastu purush. If this pada is disrespected, then demonic qualities arise in the inhabitants\"}', 'ॐ येरुपाणिप्रतिमुंचमानाऽ असुराः संत: स्वधयाचरंति। परापुरोनिपुरोयेभरन्त्यग्निष्ठाँल्लोकात्प्रणुदात्य स्मात्।। ॐ भूर्भुवः स्वर्भो असुर इहा ॐ असुरायनमः।।', 'assets/devtas/Asura W6.jpg', '{\"1\":\"Mayavi Asur, ehich is out of rhythm, Out of harmony\",\"2\":\"Gives knowledge and light if balanced\",\"3\":\"It imparts that attraction, that lure in the residents of space that he is able to feel attracted or attract opportunities for success for a longer time.\",\"4\":\"Asur provides that attraction to the personalities of Varun so that Varun as a resident is more attracted to the others and hence he becomes more saleable or presentable.\",\"5\":\"That emotion, that feel that makes the person centre of attraction. People like them, like to attach with such person.\",\"6\":\"Imbalance creates illusion.\",\"7\":\"Leads to Anti-social work\",\"8\":\"Uses wrong methods to get things done\",\"9\":\"If balanced, it makes people charming, helps them attract masses.\",\"10\":\"If a person sleeps here, he achieves an attractive personality, if it\'s balanced becomes very alluring.  But can also be in depression. They are generally mentally strong\",\"11\":\"Toilet here – males are not found to be charming or alluring.\",\"12\":\"So toilet can be in Shosh in spite of Asur.\",\"13\":\"All the negative powers, the opponents of God, people with fighting spirit are basically Asur. But, he is an attendant of Varun.\",\"14\":\"Asur gives depth to spirituality. When a person out of realization of futility, explores the depth of spirituality, at that time the power which makes him realize the futility is of Asur; it is not divine.\",\"15\":\"Asur helps in releasing mind from temptations and false hopes and in moving on a divine spiritual path.\",\"16\":\"Dev always lure you; give you ego, savour but Asur make it savour less.\"}', '{\"name\":\"Asura\",\"color\":\"Red\",\"direction\":\"WNW\",\"C1\":\"Magical/Illusionist \",\"C2\":\"Manomaya Kosha\",\"C3\":\"Left Back/Banyi Pasharva\",\"C4\":\" Agya/Alpha \"}'),
(19, 'Brahma', '{\"p1\":\"Brahma is the most significant lord in the Vaastu chakra. He rules over the biggest area in terms of padas. He owns the nine centermost padas in the Ekasheeti vaastu mandala. Brahma, the benefic universal father is the first of the omnipotent trinity of Hindu gods and appears as the great cosmic creator. In the epic Puranic times, the Vedic triad of Indra-Agni-Surya lost their preeminence to the all encompassing resonance of the magnificent trinity of Brahma-Vishnu-Shiva. Brahma is the eternal creator who creates not just the earth and all its creatures but also the heavens, the gods and the demons.\",\"p2\":\"Brahma lives in Brahmanda or the Universe. His abode is Mount Meru, which is the centre of the world and is shaped like a wheel. Brahma represents the rajas guna from which all creativity emanates. He is the universal intellect, the thought process from which the universe rises. He is the creator of the four Vedas.\",\"p3\":\"From the powers of the mind Brahma created four types of beings. Out of his thighs came the demons, from his mouth the gods, from his sides the ancestors, and lastly the humans were born out of his body which split into two - the male and the female.\",\"p4\":\"When Brahma awakes, the three worlds are created. When he sleeps there is chaos. His sons are Sanat-kumara, Sananda, Sanaka and Sanatana. His other manas sons include Marichi, Atri, Pulastya, Pulaha, kratu, Angira, Bhrigu, Vashishtha, Daksha, Kardama and Narada.\"}', 'ॐआब्रह्मन्ब्राह्मणो ब्रह्मवर्चसीजायतामाष्टेराजन्यः शूरऽइषव्या तिव्याधीमहारथोजायतां दोग्धी धेनुर्वो सप्ति:पुरंधिर्योषाजिष्णुरथेष्ठाः सभेयोयुवास्ययजमानस्यवीरोण जायतान्निकामेनिकामेनः पर्जन्योवर्षतुफल वत्योनऽ ओषधयः पच्यंतांयोगक्षेमोनः कल्पताम् ॐ भूर्भुवः स्वर्भोब्रह्मन्निहागच्छइहतिष्ठ। ब्रह्माणमावाह यामिस्थापयामि ॐब्रह्मणे नमः।।', 'assets/devtas/BRAHAMA CENTRE.jpg', '{}', '{\"name\":\"\",\"color\":\"\",\"direction\":\"\",\"C1\":\"\",\"C2\":\"\",\"C3\":\"\",\"C4\":\"\"}'),
(20, 'Mitra', '{\"p1\":\"Mitra is one of the twelve Adityas and he is the son of Kashyap and Godmother Aditi. He rules over friendship. He is closely intertwined with Varuna like milk and water. He is saluted in the vedic mantras with Varuna. Varuna always stays with Mitra and they also find reference in the Vedas. Mitra\'s qualities have also been compared to Savita. It is interesting to note that Vishnu followed Mitra\'s rules to measure the three worlds in three steps. Mitra is a day lord and Varuna a night one. Except for this they are the same. So this makes Mitra a Sun god. The Sun at twilight is Mitra. He is a beneficial force.\",\"p2\":\"In the Vaastu mandala, Mitra is placed in the west next to Varuna, Asura and Pushpadanta. He rules the left abdomen of the Vaastu Purush. Varuna and Mitra get together to generate the life force in living beings.\"}', 'ॐन्मित्रस्य वरुणस्याभिचक्षेसूर्योरुपं कृणुतेद्योरुपस्थे। अनन्तमन्यद्रुशदस्यपाजः कृष्णमन्यद्धरित: संभरन्ति। ॐभू भो मित्र इहा। मित्रायनमः।।', 'assets/devtas/MITRA W1 W8.jpg', '{\"1\":\"The change on two levels--internal and external\",\"2\":\"Vitatha shows what we show to the world and Yama shows who we are\",\"3\":\"It\'s the one that brings this world in action.\",\"4\":\"This is an inspirational energy and affectionate devta who has the capability to bind--who keeps the world tied together.\",\"5\":\"He is the power of holding the world together so that the process of evolution or manifestation could move ahead.\",\"6\":\"The seed is sown, the child is born, he is connected to the world, now he needs friends, with whom this life goes on and on.\"}', '{\"name\":\"Mitra\",\"color\":\"Red\",\"direction\":\"West\",\"C1\":\"Inspiration/Motivator\",\"C2\":\"Pranamay Kosha\",\"C3\":\"Agya/Alpha\",\"C4\":\"Saturn\"}'),
(21, 'Aryama', '{\"p1\":\"Aryama is the son of Godmother Aditi. He is also the ruler of the Uttaraphalguni nakshatra. Aryama is the leader of the pitars or forefathers and is himself a pitar. If he is appeased during the period of the Shraddha paksha, it is believed that all the pitars have been appeased. He protects the growth of a family. If he is pleased then the family tree grows. As he is the father of friends, his happiness ensures progress in spiritual alliances. In a yajna, he accepts the offering of swaha along with Mitra and Varuna and in a shraddha ceremony he accepts the svadha offering.\",\"p2\":\"Being a son of Kashyap and Aditi, he gets the yajna part. He is placed in the south in the vaastu mandala. If an inauspicious construction takes place in his pada, he causes accidents\"}', 'ॐअर्यम्णं बृहस्पतिमिद्रं दानाय चोदय वाचविष्णु सरस्वती सवितारंचवाजिनठ स्वाहा ॐ भू भो अर्यमन्निहा ॐअर्यम्णेनमः।।', 'assets/devtas/MITRA W1 W8.jpg', '{\"1\":\"After manifestation, it helps to grow\",\"2\":\"Metaphorically, when the child is born, he needs to connect with the rest of the material in the world. by all means(Sam,daam,danda, bhed) \",\"3\":\"Aryama grants connectivity with the world and has been invoked as a devta to get a bride for the groom\",\"4\":\"The power that connects with the world, gets you a companion, in order to carry ahead the process of evolution, is the power of Aryama.\"}', '{\"name\":\"Aryama\",\"color\":\"Yellow\",\"direction\":\"East\",\"C1\":\"Tuning/Connector\",\"C2\":\"Annamaya Kosha\",\"C3\":\"Right Chest/Dahina Stan\",\"C4\":\"Muladhar/Beta\",\"C5\":\"Ruby/Sun\"}');
