(22, 'Savita', '{\"p1\":\"Savita refers to the rays of the Sun that divide the day into morning and noon. Lord Savitra thus emerges from the East in the form of the Sun\'s rays called Savita. He is the radiant one. He is one of the most important of the celestial Vedic gods who is the source of life and healing. Savita means to motivate and as he rides across the sky, he infuses energy in all living beings, removes all evil dreams and vanquishes the demons. The Aditya placed in the dyuloka or heaven is also called Savita.\",\"p2\":\"When we move from the kendra padas of Brahma and move towards the south east corner, then we come across the pada for Savita between Anil and Brahma. The balance karmas of the previous birth can be analyzed from this section.\"}', 'सूर्य रश्मिर्हरिकेशः पुरस्तात्सविता ज्योतिरुदयाँ 2अजस्रम्।।', 'assets/devtas/Savita E7E8.jpg', '{\"1\":\"It bestows us the power of meditation, remover of obstacles.\",\"2\":\"It kindles fire, helps to initiate things\",\"3\":\"Activate powers in something through cleansing or through friction.\",\"4\":\"It develops association with influential and powerful people and friends, and also provides support and money.\",\"5\":\"This zone is capable of giving solutions for any type of problems\",\"6\":\"When balanced, will give support , determination, money, strength and will power\",\"7\":\"Ganesh ji presence in this zone is very good here, It carries our activities to next level.\"}', '{\"name\":\"SAVITA\",\"color\":\"Blue\",\"direction\":\"SE1\",\"C1\":\"Drive/Igniter\",\"C2\":\"Pranmaya Kosha\",\"C3\":\"Finger of Hand/Hatheli ki Ungli\",\"C4\":\"Manipur/Beta\",\"C5\":\"Cat’s Eye\"}'),
(23, 'Vivasvan', '{\"p1\":\"Vivasvan is a form of the midday Sun god. He is one of the 12 Adityas and the father of Yama, the god of death. He was married to Sangya (also known as Saranyu), daughter of Tvashta and his children are Yama, Yami and Manu. He occupies a prominent position as in the South. If a main room is constructed here, it brings gain of position and wealth\",\"p2\":\"Being a son of Kashyap and Aditi, he gets the yajna part. He is placed in the south in the vaastu mandala. If an inauspicious construction takes place in his pada, he causes accidents\"}', 'ॐविवस्वन्नादित्यैषतेसोमपीथस्तस्मिन्मत्स्व श्रदस्मै नरोव्वचसेदधात नयदाशीर्दादंपतिमिमश्नुतः। पुमान्पुत्रोजायतेव्विंदतेव्वस्वधाव्विश्वाहारपऽएधतेगृहे। ॐभू भोविवस्वन्निहा ॐविवस्वतेनमः।।', 'assets/devtas/VIVASVAN S1 S8.jpg', '{\"1\":\"The change on two levels--internal and external\",\"2\":\"Vitatha shows what we show to the world and Yama shows who we are\",\"3\":\"It controls the change from which existence starts initiate.\",\"4\":\"It shines that change and moves the manifestation process.\"}', '{\"name\":\"Vivasvan\",\"color\":\"red\",\"direction\":\"South\",\"C1\":\"Extrovert/Change Controller\",\"C2\":\"Pranamaya Kosha\",\"C3\":\"Right Stomach/Dahina Amashaya (Pet)\",\"C4\":\" Manipur/Beta\",\"C5\":\"Moonga/Mars\"}'),
(24, 'Mahendra', '{\"p1\":\"He is the biggest of the 12 Adityas and is the eldest son of Godmother Aditi. He was also called Kulishayudh, meaning he whose weapon is the thunderbolt. According to the Rig Vedas, Mahendra is imbibed with three qualities of doing great work, incomparable valor and vanquisher of demons. Indra is considered to be lower in hierarchy than the Sun.\",\"p2\":\"His thunderbolt Vajra and his bow Indradhanush protect mankind from the vagaries of nature, symbolized by the demons. Thus he is both revered as the God of rains and feared as the God of the storms. He is the ruler of the atmosphere and weathers are at his command. In spite of his powerful arsenal of weapons, Indra, lord of the sky is a peaceful, heavenly ruler who offers refuge to all those who seek him and follow the path of Dharma. He is one of the powerful triad of Agni, Indra and Surya and is an important atmospheric or madhyam sthana deity. His consort is Indrani.\",\"p3\":\"In the Vaastu chakra, Indra rules the cell next to the centermost cell in the East and next to the Sun god if we move from East to north east.\"}', 'ॐमहारैऽएइंद्रोवज्रहस्त: षोडशीशर्मसच्छतु हन्तुपाप्मानयोस्मान्दृष्टि। उप यामगृहीतोसिमहेंद्रायत्वैषतेयोनिर्महेंद्रायत्वा। ॐ भूर्भुवः स्वः भोः कुलिशायुध इहागच्छइहतिष्ठ ॐकुलिशायुधाय नमः।।', 'assets/devtas/Mahendera E4.jpg', '{\"1\":\"Great association, powerful contacts, luxury, grants money.\",\"2\":\"Entrance here gives monetary benefits from influential people, people enjoy life of luxury and comfort.\",\"3\":\"If one needs powerful contacts, one needs to treat this zone.\",\"4\":\"Balance Varun and Yama along with Indra as they are his brothers\",\"5\":\"Ruby on floor is very beneficial here.\",\"6\":\"Table chair in office here gives top position in company.\",\"7\":\"If zone is balanced, put Ashoka Pillar. Gives Government related benefits.\",\"8\":\"No recognition of efforts if there is a toilet. Family will be looked down upon.\",\"9\":\"Powerful connections with bedroom here.\",\"10\":\"Living room here gives beneficial connections.\",\"11\":\"Sleeping here changes ones temperament, Likes to associate with best in society.\",\"12\":\"NO BLACK colour in this region. (Black represents Shani who is Sun’s enemy)\",\"13\":\"Presence of orange colour in this field gives positive result.\",\"14\":\"If cut, people can make lot of money due to other balanced zones, but they have to deal with very ordinary people.\"}', '{\"name\":\"Mahendra(E4)\",\"color\":\"Green\",\"direction\":\"East\",\"C1\":\" Organizing/Administrator\",\"C2\":\"Pranmaya Kosha\",\"C3\":\"Right Shoulder/Dahina Skandh\",\"C4\":\"Manipur/Alpha\",\"C5\":\"Ruby\"}'),
(25, 'Surya', '{\"p1\":\"Surya is considered as one of the most important of the 12 Adityas. As the giver of food, sight, health, knowledge and intelligence, he is the greatest of the Adityas. He is a source of powerful energy, providing the life force and rescuing the world from the fear of darkness and disease. He is the maker of the day. He is the celestial Vedic god who is the source of life and healing. He is the all seeing god and is described as the eyes of Varuna and Mitrfqea during the day. He is seen as the precursor of the trinity - the concept of God as creator, preserver and destroyer. He represents the cycle of birth, life and death, fertilizing the earth with its warmth and giving new life. His energy provides life and his heat burns everything in the end.\",\"p2\":\"In the Ekasheetipada, he rules the centermost cell on the eastern horizon and there is evidence that the Shree Graha (main area where the owner\'s wealth emerges) is located on this part of the Vaastu Purush.\"}', 'ॐरश्मिर्हरिकेशः पुरतात् सविताज्योतिरुदयाँ अजस्रम्। तस्य पूषाप्रसवे यातिविद्वान् सम्पश्यन् विश्वाभुवनानिगोपाः। | ॐ भूर्भुवः स्वः सूर्यइहागच्छइहतिष्ठ ॐसूर्याय नमः।।', 'assets/devtas/Surya E5.jpg', '{\"1\":\"Atma or Soul\",\"2\":\"Guardian Power and Controller of System\",\"3\":\"Farsightedness and increases Observation Power\",\"4\":\"Controls comes with great observation.\",\"5\":\"Chief of 9 planets\",\"6\":\"Depicted by 7 horses chariot\",\"7\":\"It balances energy and strength of the residents, fame and recognition in the society.\",\"8\":\"Door here gives short temperament and aggressive behaviour\",\"9\":\"If imbalanced and  boss is sitting here, he feels work environment is not in his control\",\"10\":\"Poster or Murti of lord Vishnu here is very beneficial here\",\"11\":\"Presence of Copper Sun is advisable when overall fire element is weak. Even if East is also weak, copper sun can be used.\",\"12\":\"Brass sun is very beneficial\",\"13\":\"If energy is weak, men of the house are very mellow, not that responsible and of strong personality.\",\"14\":\"Kitchen brings aggression and temper\",\"15\":\"Orange colour positive result.\",\"16\":\"Things will not be very systematic and organised if this field is weak.\",\"17\":\"Weak energy can lead to lack of sex drive in men.\",\"18\":\"If the owner of the house complains that “nobody listens to me”, then check this filed.\",\"19\":\"Temple is good here\",\"20\":\"If cut, men are mellow, things are chaotic; men are not leaders of house.\",\"21\":\"This is the medium door in East direction. It gives aggression. For complete growth, we need a proper amount of sun energy. This door is not good for industries. Owner insults important employees due to excessive aggression, which results in miscommunication and deficits. It is not everyone\'s cup of tea to withstand the supreme energy of sun, only people with higher authorities and very big social circle can contain it.\"}', '{\"name\":\"Surya(E5)\",\"color\":\"Blue\",\"direction\":\"East\",\"C1\":\" Observer/Controller\",\"C2\":\"Pranmaya Kosha\",\"C3\":\"Right Hand/Dahina Haath\",\"C4\":\"Manipur/Alpha\"}'),
(26, 'Varuna', '{\"p1\":\"Varuna is the celestial Vedic god of the sky and keeper of the divine order of things. With the rise of Indra as supreme deity, he became the lord of the rivers and oceans. In the Vedas he is said to be the creator and sustainer of the universe and administrator of the cosmic law. Day and night appear at his bidding and the rivers are channeled according to his plans. Varuna avenges sin and falsehood and his eye is the Sun who keeps a watch on everything. He is the upholder of moral and ethical laws. He is the chief of the lower celestial deities called Adityas. He is regent of the west. He carries a rope to bind sinners with, symbolic of a man being fettered by his sins. Varuna is said to be gracious even to him who has committed sin. In the Mahabharata, he is lord of the waves and of rivers, god of fluidity and movement. Being a god of the rivers, he is propitiated in times of drought and for protection from the dangers of the waters.\",\"p2\":\"It is said that Varuna forgives a person who repents. His forgiveness and anger extends to the forefathers also. That is why jala tarpan or water is offered to ancestors.\",\"p3\":\"He occupies the left thigh of the Vaastu purush in the west direction.\"}', 'इमम्मेवरुणश्रुधीहवमद्याचमृडय। त्वामवस्युराचके।। ॐ भूर्भुवः स्वर्भोवरुणइहा वरुणायनमः।।', 'assets/devtas/Varuna W5.jpg', '{\"1\":\"God of water and Oceans\",\"2\":\"As Sun is important in East, Varun is important in West.\",\"3\":\"Varun possesses extraordinary powers. He has wisdom which has been termed as \'Maaya\'. He controls enemies through his paash.\",\"4\":\"Varun controls your tendencies (Cvrittiya) through his paash and bound with that paash, that drive, a person keeps on running.\",\"5\":\"Varun is the granter of immortality.\",\"6\":\"All the rules in the world are created by Varun only. All the principles which are followed by devtas, humans and energy fields(to execute their dharma) are created and maintained by Varun.\",\"7\":\"Varun is very merciful on people who confess and repent. He grants growth and prosperity also.\",\"8\":\"Varun\'s paash are not always used negatively. they also work as a supporting power to bind together a bride and bridegroom.\",\"9\":\"In Vastu Purush Mandala, Number 5 devtas like varun, Surya, Yama, Soma are like top bosses(master minds), helps us manifest things in their domains. Devtas number3,4 in every direction works like assistants.\",\"10\":\"Varun is associated with Nakshatra Shatbhisha. this nakshatra is symbol of black, Black is saturn and circle is metal so black Circle is a good remedy here.\",\"11\":\"Ability to see, Vision. It is said Varun has thousand eyes, Indra has hundred and we have two. Here Indra is combination of Surya and Mahendra. \",\"12\":\"Give the energy to give the best performance in all tasks.\",\"13\":\"Sleeping here makes a person perfectionist and over ambitious. But able to see better , observe better the faults of others.\",\"14\":\"Good financial position If entrance here but perfectionist and over ambitious attitude.\",\"15\":\"Dining table here gives good digestion.\",\"16\":\"Water and blue colour gives prosperity and good fortune.\"}', '{\"name\":\"Varun(E5)\",\"color\":\"Red\",\"direction\":\"West\",\"C1\":\"Charge/Observational Power\",\"C2\":\"Manomaya Kosha\",\"C3\":\" Left Thigh/Banyi Jaangh \",\"C4\":\"Sastrar/Delta\",\"C5\":\"Neelam\"}'),
(27, 'satya', '{\"p1\":\"Satya is one of the Ashta vasus called Pratyush and is the son of Dharma and Vasu, the daughter of Prajapati Daksha. He is the reincarnation of religion and confers steadfastness and commitment in action. Pratyush means dawn and is closely related to the Sun. He is endowed with the qualities of awakening and is considered to be beneficial.\",\"p2\":\"He rules the cell next to the centermost cell in the east, if we move from east to south east. He is an inviolable, imperishable and eternal being, whose unvarying and dependable course symbolizes truth, stability and steadfastness.\"}', 'ॐव्रतेनदीक्षामाप्नोति दक्षिणाम्। दक्षिणाश्रद्धामाप्नोतिश्रद्धयास त्यमाप्यते।। ॐ भूर्भुवः स्वः भोसत्यइहा ॐसत्यायनमः।।', 'assets/devtas/Satya E 6.jpg', '{\"1\":\"Goodwill and credibility creator\",\"2\":\"Attributes very close to Surya\",\"3\":\"It imparts the power of thinking\",\"4\":\"Encourages fulfilling commitment.\",\"5\":\"Biggest commitment is Marriage. So this zone needs to be balanced and thus relations will be balanced\",\"6\":\"Imbalance here will make the person to move from one partner to another.\",\"7\":\"Mirror, reddish color is very dangerous here.\",\"8\":\"Entrance here, not only we fail in keeping our commitments but others also fail to fulfil their commitment towards us.\",\"9\":\"Green plants are ok but blue colour is bad. People will not fulfil their promise.\"}', '{\"name\":\"Satya(E6)\",\"color\":\"red\",\"direction\":\"ESE\",\"C1\":\"Ego/Goodwill creator\",\"C2\":\"Annamaya Kosha \",\"C3\":\"Right Hand/Dahina Haath\",\"C4\":\"Swadhisthan/Beta\",\"C5\":\"Ruby\"}'),
(28, 'Pushpdanta', '{\"p1\":\"Pushpadanta was one of the ganas of the Gandharva community. He knew the science of becoming invisible. He once used this skill to overhear a story being related by Shankar to Parvati. On being discovered, he begged for forgiveness\",\"p2\":\"It is said that Varuna forgives a person who repents. His forgiveness and anger extends to the forefathers also. That is why jala tarpan or water is offered to ancestors.\",\"p3\":\"His pada is one in the series of padas promoting studies and practice.\"}', 'ॐनक्षत्रेभ्यः स्वाहा नक्षत्रियेभ्यः स्वाहाहोरात्रेभ्यः स्वाहार्धमासेभ्यः स्वाहा मासेभ्यः स्वाहा ऋतुभ्यः स्वाहातवेभ्यः स्वाहा संवत्सरायस्वाहा द्यावा पृथिवीभ्यां स्वाहा चंद्रायस्वाहा सूर्यायस्वाहा रश्मिभ्यः स्वाहा वसुभ्यः स्वाहा रुद्रेभ्यः स्वाहादित्येभ्यः स्वाहा मरुदभ्यः स्वाहा विश्वेभ्योदेवेभ्यः स्वाहा मूलेभ्यः स्वाहा शाखाभ्यः स्वाहा वनस्पतिभ्यः स्वाहा पुष्पेभ्यः स्वाहा फलेभ्यः स्वाहौषधीभ्यः स्वाहा ॐभू पुष्पदंतइहा ॐपुष्पदंताय नमः।।', 'assets/devtas/Pushpdanta W4.jpg', '{\"1\":\"Power of blessing.\",\"2\":\"In Hindu mythology, Shiv Mahima Strota is written by Gandharva Pushpdant.\",\"3\":\"the work of gandharva is to keep association between the humans and Gods.\",\"4\":\"Gives the power to overcome day to day problems.\",\"5\":\"Imbalance cause inability to conduct day to day matters\",\"6\":\"Gaja Lakshmi is a very good remedy here. It provides her vibrations to enjoy life of luxury and prosperity.\",\"7\":\"Entrance here give all kind of assistance, general happiness in life.\",\"8\":\"Bedroom gives great opportunities and makes one successful, gives feeling that entire universe is helping.\",\"9\":\"Living room with Black colour sofa and black tv makes all deals and discussions fruitful. Black means Shani.\",\"10\":\"Toilet here, you will not receive help from friends in the time of need.\",\"11\":\"White flowers in water are a great remedy here. Green plants are not permissible.\",\"12\":\"Blue colour/presence of water give good results\",\"13\":\"Safe (Tijori) – best place. Money comes with smooth flow.\",\"14\":\"This is a friendly energy field which helps us to succeed in all respective domains.\",\"15\":\"If balanced, help from all sides. It grants the power to fulfill all the desires in life; success and growth.\",\"16\":\"Vastu shastramentions about Ashta Luxmi: 1. Adi Luxmi  --  Gives us heritage(Sampatti)  --  South 2. Dhan Luxmi  --  Gives us money/gold  --  Southeast 3. Dhanya Luxmi  --  Gives us grains  --  Southwest 4. Gaja Luxmi  --  Power of Royalty(like Indra)  --  West 5. Santan Luxmi  --  Offsprings  --  Northeast 6. Virya/Dhairya Luxmi  --  courage/Strength  -- 7. Vijay Luxmi  --  Victory  --  Northwest 8. Vidhya Luxmi  --  Knowledge  --\"}', '{\"name\":\"Pushpdant(W4)\",\"color\":\"blue\",\"direction\":\"West\",\"C1\":\"Exploring/Assisting Power\",\"C2\":\"Manomaya Kosha\",\"C3\":\"Left Knee/Banya Ghutna\",\"C4\":\"Swadhisthan/Beta\",\"C5\":\"Neelam\"}'),
(29, 'Nabh', '{\"p1\":\"Lord Nabh is instated as the sky. He is synonymous with space or universe and Usha is considered to be his daughter. According to Matsya Purana, he is one of the eight forms of Lord Shankara. The sky is the source of breeze or wind and he is actually the lord himself, without whom none can survive. The sky is all pervasive and made up of the units of Ghatakash, Mathakash and Mahakash.\",\"p2\":\"In the Vaastu chakra, he rules the pada which is located in the south east towards the east direction. This is a very significant location because it symbolizes the sky, and it is vacant or without a lord. It is said that when the different gods occupied different parts of the vaastu purush under the orders of Brahma, no one got rulership of the right palm because of the aggressive nature of the Vaastu purush. Brahmaji then imposed the rule that this area is without a lord and the Vaastu purush is free to use his right hand according to his own wish, to punish or bless. So at the time of house warming, Vaastu deva is installed in this pada and he blesses the inhabitants.\"}', '| ॐवयंसोमव्रतेतवमनस्तनूषुबिभ्रतः। प्रजावन्तः सचेमहि। ॐ भूर्भुवः स्वः भोआकाशइहागच्छ ॐआकाशायनमः।।', 'assets/devtas/Nabh Antriksh E8.jpg', '{\"1\":\"Space between earth and heaven\",\"2\":\"This is the oxygen needed to make anything happen.\",\"3\":\"Manifestation of even is possible only through Akash\",\"4\":\"If this are stuck (Atak gaya hai), like payment or marriage, then look at this zone.\",\"5\":\"Entrance causes financial losses, accidents, burglary\",\"6\":\"If you keep anything here, people will recognise it and appreciate it.\",\"7\":\"If this zone is weak, cause high chances of theft.\",\"8\":\"Sri Yantra if kept here gives great result.\",\"9\":\"Placement of red bulb is good, Gives aggression and body rashes if imbalanced.\",\"10\":\"Copper studs are good to balance this zone.\",\"11\":\"Field of Venus, thus affects females more than males if imbalanced\",\"12\":\"Cut in this field, elder son of the house is away from home and not a part of the family.\",\"13\":\"Recommend Diamond in this field but should be astrologically examined\",\"14\":\"If there is a store, it adversely effects the happy events in life.\"}', '{\"name\":\"AKASH (E7)\",\"color\":\"Yellow\",\"direction\":\"SE\",\"C1\":\"Allowing/Inner space\",\"C2\":\"Manomaya Kosha\",\"C3\":\"Anahat/Beta\",\"C4\":\"Diamond\"}'),
(30, 'PUSHA', '{\"p1\":\"Pusha is one of the 12 Adityas, son of Rishi Kashyapa and Devi Aditi. He is the father of all animals and rides a goat. In the Vaastuchkara he occupies the pada towards the South, when we move from the South east. In the Yajna by Daksha, he lost his teeth and eyes to Veerbhadra. Thereafter he sees through the eyes of the Sun. He is firm in the milky way and helps enhance wealth in the form of animals. He gets the Yajna pada and is capable of granting boons. Powdered rice is offered to him.\",\"p2\":\"Pusha is a symbol of weak mentality because if this pada is corrupt then cheating, pride and fraud arise in a person.\"}', 'ॐ पूषन्तवव्रतेवयं नरिष्येमकदाचन। स्तोतारस्तऽइहस्मसि। ॐ भूर्भुवः स्वः भो पूषन्निहागच्छ इहतिष्ठ। ॐ पूष्णेनमः।।', 'assets/devtas/Pusha S2.jpg', '{\"1\":\"This field  is nourishing like mother nourishes a child\",\"2\":\"Best place to keep Ghee\",\"3\":\"Elderly, Strength, Blocked Payment, Power to recover from Losses\",\"4\":\"Safeguard of everything including money\",\"5\":\"If payment blocked. Check this zone.\",\"6\":\"This becomes the fuel to continue the fire.\",\"7\":\"Keep a Red Mat here to get back blocked money.\",\"8\":\"If the child growth is not satisfactory in the mother’s womb, keep a red mat and Ghee for best results.\",\"9\":\"Imbalance causes problem in family bonding.\",\"10\":\"Family photos kept here increases the bonding here strongly amongst the family members\",\"11\":\"Blue colour here shows weakened body.\",\"12\":\"Children will not be self sufficient if imbalance here.\",\"13\":\"A person will work under someone if this zone is imbalanced.\",\"14\":\"Toilet here will cause bad growth of child.\",\"15\":\"Keep a Fevicol tube to improve family bonding.\",\"16\":\"Keep a Hanuman Ji photo showing strength there.\",\"17\":\"Pusha is invoked along with Indra to block the enemy.\",\"18\":\"Pusha provides never say die attitude. A person is able to successfully overcome any obstacle with strength.\",\"19\":\"Entrance here take person to work in MNC, gives growth in job. Leads to slavery of others and bondage.\",\"20\":\"Pusha considers family bonding, growth, self sufficiency, recovery of money, or ability to remerge, don\'t lose hope.\",\"21\":\"Pusha also invoked to impart power to select the bridegroom.\"}', '{\"name\":\"Pusha(S2)\",\"color\":\"blue\",\"direction\":\"SSE\",\"C1\":\"Elderly/Strengthener\",\"C2\":\"Annamaya Kosha\",\"C3\":\"Right wrist/Dahini Kalai\",\"C4\":\"Swadhisthan/Alpha\"}'),
(31, 'Bhrisha', '{\"p1\":\"The name Bhrisha means excess or extension. This pada is ruled by a goddess named Usha and her qualities are synonymous with the meaning of Bhrisha. The 20 sutras of Rig Veda praise the Goddess Usha. She is the personification of beauty. The sky lights us when she awakens and the universe is filled with happiness. She is the lady love of Surya and emerges from the east in her attractive attire. The Vedas call Usha the mother of the Sun, because she emerges with the Sun in her lap. Usha is worshipped for attractive appearance, discipline, progress and prosperity.\",\"p2\":\"In the Vaastu chakra, Bhrisha rules the pada which is located in the south east towards the east direction.\"}', 'ॐ भद्रं कर्णेभिः श्रृणुयामदेवाभद्रपश्येमाक्षभिर्यजत्राः।। स्थिरैरङ्गैस्तुष्टुवां सस्मनूभिर्व्यशेमहिदेवहितंयदायुः। ॐ भूर्भुवः स्वः भो भृश इहागच्छ ॐभृशायनमः।।', 'assets/devtas/Bhrisha E7.jpg', '{\"1\":\"Brings out something by rubbing two things\",\"2\":\"Analysis, Poor Implementation of Plan, Delay/hastiness in Decisions, gravity\",\"3\":\"Action will not be executed if this field is weak\",\"4\":\"Will think excessively if this is weak so end result will be disturbed. \",\"5\":\"Can be balanced by keeping Mixer-Grinder\",\"6\":\"Analytical capability is disturbed if this is weak\",\"7\":\"A cut here will not lead to any decision\",\"8\":\"This zone can be balanced with White colour\",\"9\":\"This is Kama Devta, energy of Desires\",\"10\":\"Blue colour worst here\",\"11\":\"Presence of sewerage gives unfavourable here.\",\"12\":\"Metallic show pieces not desirable\",\"13\":\"Sewing machine here leads to BP fluctuation and anxiety.\",\"14\":\"Elderly couple sleeping here – wife will be continuously ill\",\"15\":\"If the thinking is not good, examine this field\",\"16\":\"If boss is sitting here, he is very strict and thus leads to problems in the future\",\"17\":\"Dustbin not desirable here\",\"18\":\"Kamdhenu to be placed here\",\"19\":\"Entrance here gives insensitive behaviour\",\"20\":\"Muladhar--foundation, insecurity, basic stability\",\"21\":\"Annamaya Kosha--body\",\"22\":\"Beta wave--day to day functioning\",\"23\":\"Washing machine is good here\",\"24\":\"Kitchen her imbalance it and can sent a person in coma.\",\"25\":\"Toilet is okay here.\"}', '{\"name\":\"BRISHA(E7)\",\"color\":\"Green\",\"direction\":\"ESE\",\"C1\":\"Honing/Gravity\",\"C2\":\"Annamaya Kosha\",\"C3\":\"Middle hand/Madhya bhuja\",\"C4\":\"Muladhar/Beta\"}'),
(32, 'ANIL', '{\"p1\":\"Anil is actually a synonym for wind. He is known as Vaata devata in the Rig Veda. He is one of the Ashtavasus. He is established in the south east direction and controls the right hand palm of the Vaastu purush. Anil was born from the womb of Vasu, daughter of Prajapati Daksha, wife of Dharma. Wind and sky are closely related. That is why Anil has been stationed next to Nabh. He symbolizes the wind on earth. Vayu is born from the dhatu Va and means motion. This pada is good for fire related activities like havan etc as Anil helps the movement of the fire. Vayu is the soul of the Gods and resides in every living being as breath.\"}', 'ॐआवायो भूषशुचिपाऽउपनः सहस्रं ते नियुतोविश्ववार। उहोते अंधो मद्यमयामि सस्यदेवदधिषेपूर्वपेयम् वायवेत्वा।। ॐ भूर्भुवः स्वः भोवायो इहागच्छइहतिष्ठ ॐवायवे नमः।।', 'assets/devtas/Anil S1.jpg', '{\"1\":\"Venus is the planet\",\"2\":\"Lord of Wind energy\",\"3\":\"If someone says, the work is not even starting “kaam shuru hi nahi ho raha hai”, then check this\",\"4\":\"Door here effects the elder son negatively.\",\"5\":\"Semen count is less in case of childbirth if this is disturbed\",\"6\":\"Sleeping may cause restlessness in females.\",\"7\":\"Presence of yellow colour causes heavy cash crunch.\",\"8\":\"When things are not expanding as expected, need to check this zone.\"}', '{\"name\":\"ANIL(S1)\",\"color\":\"Yellow\",\"direction\":\"SE\",\"C1\":\"Awakening/Up lifter \",\"C2\":\"Right Elbow/Dahini Kohni\",\"C3\":\"Agya/Alpha\",\"C4\":\"Diamond\",\"C5\":\"Vigyanmaya Kosha\"}'),
