(34, 'Yama', '{\"p1\":\"Yama is the son of Surya and Sangya. Yama is the God of death and is the lord of infernal regions one visits after the cessation of life. He is the embodiment of the rule of law and imparts justice according to deeds. The word Yama means the restrainer. It is he who keeps mankind in check. In the Vedas, Yama is the first ancestor and has a full distinction of a God. Yama was earlier a mere mortal who gained immortality in order to become a god. He is the god of departed spirits and judge of the dead. He gathers all the souls of the dead and guides them to the netherworld, which he rules as God of the dead.\",\"p2\":\"Yama or Dharmaraja is a fair and impartial judge. When a mortal faces him, his evil and good deeds are read out and Yama weighs them and pronounces judgements, as to whether the person goes to pitrilok or heaven or one of the twenty one hells or be reborn on earth. He is invoked during sacrifices to come with the deified souls of the fathers to bless the performer of the sacrifice. Yama or dikpala rules the South and he is appeased by lighting earthen lamps in memory of ancestors or pitars.\"}', 'यमायत्वामखायत्वासूर्यस्यत्वातपसे देवस्त्वासविता मध्वानक्तपृथिव्याः सं स्पृशस्पाहि। अर्चिरसिशोचिरसितपोसि। ॐ भूर्भुवः स्वः भो यम इहा ॐ यमाय नमः।।', 'assets/devtas/Yama S5.jpg', '{\"1\":\"Denotes self control and moral duty.\",\"2\":\"Imparts a sense of responsibility\",\"3\":\"Makes right choices and lead a discipline life.\",\"4\":\"Ruling planet is Mars\",\"5\":\"Lord of Justice\",\"6\":\"Individual faces weak determination and lack of self control. This leads to debts and blocked mind.\",\"7\":\"People sitting or sleeping here are self motivated and self controlled.\",\"8\":\" Imbalance here cause low morals amongst residents.\",\"9\":\"Toilet here lowers moral values\",\"10\":\"Water storage here gives a feeling of black magic.\",\"11\":\"Musical keyboard kept here makes one practice regularly.\",\"12\":\"Entrance here causes Death , b