(38, 'Mrigha', '{\"p1\":\"Although Mriga refers to a deer, a nakshatra, a month and even the Moon, in Vaastu shastra, Mriga refers to the hindu month of margashirsha. The 12 Adityas are placed in the Vaastu chakra and they represent the 12 months according to the Puranas, because they are actually symbolic of the different levels of heat generated by the Sun god. Anshu is the lord of Margashirsha month and he is assisted by Kashyapa Rishi, Urvashi, Gandharva Ritusen, Demon Vidyutachatru, Bhalla tarkshya and Naga Mahashankha.\",\"p2\":\"In the Vaastu chakra he is located on the right buttock of the Vaastu purush.\"}', ' ॐतद्दिष्णोः परमंपदर्छ सदापश्यन्ति सूरयः। दिवीवचक्षुराततम्। ॐ भूर्भुवः स्व मृगइहा ॐमृगायनमः।।', 'assets/devtas/Mriga S8.jpg', '{\"1\":\"Generator of curiosity\",\"2\":\"Imparts the ability to grasp the essence of things.\",\"3\":\"Keeps searching for satisfying his curiosity.\",\"4\":\"It helps them decode the secrets of skills.\",\"5\":\"It gives them power, strong vibrations to take this quest to higher planes of knowledge and skills. \",\"6\":\"Skills and proficiencies and raise their standards to optimal levels.\",\"7\":\"Keep study table here, people enjoy study and master the subject.\",\"8\":\"Placement of Garud is good here. Gives broader vision \",\"9\":\"Eagle here gives foresight and detailing\",\"10\":\"Toilet here diminishes  the curosities of learning and thinking\",\"11\":\"Fire here is worst thing to happen. Finishes the power to learn anything new.\",\"12\":\"Entrance here gives disconnection from family and rest of the world, also can create that person\'s skills take the back seat\",\"13\":\"Tools kept here, people explore and become master, if pen kept here, person try to become an auther.\",\"14\":\"If tv placed her, person see programs like Nat geo, BBC which improves knowledge.\",\"15\":\"Bed here, person is always curious and enthusiast to learn new things.\",\"16\":\"In ancient times, people used to work more with hands, they used to sell handmade goods to earn their livelihood. SO they required skill to improve their creations which they used to get by sleeping or working in this energy field. That\'s why this area of the building was used to make bedroom for common man in order to make optimum utilization of this power.\"}', '{\"name\":\"Mrigha(S8)\",\"color\":\"Green\",\"direction\":\"SW\",\"C1\":\"Curiosity/Curiosity giver \",\"C2\":\"Manomaya Kosha\",\"C3\":\"Right leg/Dahina per\",\"C4\":\"Agya/Alpha\"}'),
(39, 'Pitra gana', '{\"p1\":\"Pitri are the deceased ancestors to whom pindas are offered in worship. Pitri also signifies the ten Prajapatis or the mythical progenitors of the human race. The first pitris are said to be the sons of the gods. Yama was king of the Pitris. There are seven classes of the Pitris according to the Puranas. Three of them (Vairajas, Agnishwattas, Barishads) are incorporeal, without form, composed of intellectual not elementary substance, and assuming whatever forms they please. The corporeal Pitris are Sukalas, Angirasas, Suswadhas, and Somapas. The Rig Veda makes two independent classes of Pitris. The Agni dagdhas (who when alive, kept up the household flame and presented oblations with fire) and the Anagnidagdhas (who when alive, did not keep up the household flame and did not present oblations with fire).\",\"p2\":\"Although the Pitris mounted to the heavenly abode of bliss, their happiness was not altogether independent of the acts of devotion shown to them by the living. It could be greatly increased by offerings of Soma, rice, and water, for like the gods they were thought to have bodies of air-like texture, and to enjoy the subtle essence of food. Hence, the surviving children felt it a sacred duty to make feast-offerings, called Shraddhs, at stated times to their departed Pitris. In return for these acts the grateful Pitris protected them from harm and promoted their welfare.\"}', ' ॐपितृभ्यः स्वधायिभ्यः स्वधानमः।। पितामहेभ्यः स्वधायिभ्यः स्वधानमः।। प्रपितापमहेभ्यः स्वधायिभ्यः स्वधा नमः।। अक्षन्पितरोमीमदन्तपितरोतीतृपन्नपितरः पितरः शुन्धध्वम्। ॐ भूर्भुवः स्वर्भोः पितरइहागच्छतइहतिष्ठत ॐपितृभ्योनमः।।', 'assets/devtas/PITRA W1.jpg', '{\"1\":\"Responsible for childbirth and marriage\",\"2\":\"Responsible to carry forward our lineage/safety and security with life and all the comfort related to life.\",\"3\":\"Family bonding, love and understanding\",\"4\":\"Toilet here cause Pitra Dosh \",\"5\":\"Provides the strength to deal with adverse