(40, 'Dauvarika', '{\"p1\":\"Dauvarika represents a guard or watchman. In Samrangan Sutradhar, he is Nandi or the lord of the Pramath ganas. Nandi is one of the ganas of Lord Shankara. Nandi means one who sings praises to please someone. In the Vaastu chakra he is placed on the left buttock of the Vaastu purush.\"}', 'ॐद्रविणोदा: पिपीषतिजुहोत प्रचतिष्ठत।नेष्ट्राद्दतुभिरिष्यतः।। ॐभू दौवारिकइहा दौवारिकायनमः।।', 'assets/devtas/Dauvarika W2.jpg', '{\"1\":\"Decides what to enter in the life and what to leave out.\",\"2\":\"It let you indulge in unwanted thoughts or subjects and thus, Acts as filter or door keeper doesn’t in life.\",\"3\":\"Bonding, Door Keeper, Retention of Knowledge, Learning & Memory of children\",\"4\":\"Responsible for step wise knowledge.(Swadhisthan chakra--responsible choices)\",\"5\":\"Swadhisthan is about give and take, Muladhar is about hold.\",\"6\":\"Power of discretion/ discrimination\",\"7\":\"When a person complains of “total wastage of efforts”, look at Daurika also along with Bhringraj\",\"8\":\"Nandi remedy is best here for safegaurds of our savings.\",\"9\":\"Entrance here gives Insecure relationships and unstable career. \",\"10\":\"A piggy bank here  is associated with increase in savings.\",\"11\":\"Bed here makes one mindful and cautious. Better capability of recieving.\",\"12\":\"Individual received money through inheritance or lottery, can\'t remain with him, If this energy field is weak\",\"13\":\"Weak zone causes a person not to be able to use money or save money judiciously.\",\"14\":\"Toilet here makes a person waste money on useless products and services.\",\"15\":\" Study table here gives the student a right gauge of what to study and how much importance to give to a subject.\",\"16\":\"When balanced it ensures excellent studies for children. If it\'s weak, children will not be able to retain the learned knowledge, and at the time of examination, they will forget what they had learned by heart.\",\"17\":\" Village scene in black frames gives the power to decide where to invest and where not to invest.\"}', '{\"name\":\"DAUWARIK(W2)\",\"color\":\"Blue\",\"direction\":\"WSW\",\"C1\":\"Discrimination/Door keeper\",\"C2\":\"Manomaya Kosha\",\"C3\":\"Left Hip/Banya Kulha\",\"C4\":\"Muladhar/DeltaSwadhisthan/Alpha\",\"C5\":\"Gomed\"}'),
(41, 'Aapvatsa', '{\"p1\":\"Aapvatsa has been linked with the children of water bodies, namely, rivers, lakes etc. In the Vedas Aapvatsa has been specifically called the source of water, underground water, or water body above the earth\'s level. But at times he has been associated with moving water. The offspring of water is the nadichakra that emerges from water. That is why this pada in the north east is associated with water.\",\"p2\":\"When we move from the Kendra padas of Brahma and move towards the north east corner, then we come across the pada for the God called Aapvatsa.\"}', 'ॐआतेवत्सोमनोयमत्परमाच्चित्सधस्थात् अग्नेत्वांकामयागिर।। ॐ भूर्भुवः स्व आपवत्स इहा ॐआपवत्सायनमः।।', 'assets/devtas/Aapvatsa E1E2.jpg', '{\"1\":\"Apaha brings ideas, Apahavatsa carriers these ideas towards practical application, into all areas of our life. To make these ideas doable.\",\"2\":\"Son of Apaha\",\"3\":\"In practical terms, how to make usage of the insights in our day to day life.\",\"4\":\"It grants the power which carries medicinal elements to the point of disease in the human body. The same power is also responsible for carrying insights from intuitive body(vigyanmaya kosha) to mind body(manomaya kosha). That\'s why vastu recommends doing worship or meditation in this energy field.\"}', '{\"name\":\"APAHAVATSA(NE2)\",\"color\":\"Red\",\"direction\":\"WSW\",\"C1\":\"Care/Carrier\",\"C2\":\"Vigyanmaya Kosha\",\"C3\":\"Right Chest/Dahini Chhati\",\"C4\":\"Vishuddhi/Theta\",\"C5\":\"Pukhraj/Cat’s Eye\"}'),
(42, 'JAYA', '{\"p1\":\"Jaya is the lord of the pada next to Indra and positioned on the diagonal line connecting the Brahma kendra padas with the south west corner. It is a very important pada and is highly influenced by Indra. There are different schools of thought, who juxtapose the padas of Jaya and Indra. Whatever be their position, this does not undermine the significance of Jaya in the Vaastu chakra.\"}', 'ॐमम्माणितेवर्मणाछादयामिसोमस्त्वा राजामृतेनानुवस्ताम्। उरोर्वरीयोवरुणास्तेकृणोतुजयन्तन्त्वानुदेवाम दंतु।। ॐ भूर्भोजयइहा जयायनमः।।', 'assets/devtas/Jaya W1W2.jpg', '{\"1\":\"Indra is thought process adn Jaya is that channel in which the thought process can be manifested\",\"2\":\"Weapon of Indra, Vajra, all the weapons which ensures victory in life.\",\"3\":\"This power gets developed in the form of the power to impart skill and expertise.\",\"4\":\"This direction is recommended to make a place for keeping all those tools, books and objects which are related to the performance of your skills.\",\"5\":\"In any domain, field or business, your skill is your Vajra(Jaya).\",\"6\":\"If this energy field loses its power, then you feel unable to exercise your skill at the right time and at the right place.\",\"7\":\"It gives victory in life, tools and skills\",\"8\":\"When balance, you can use full potential of your capabilities.\"}', '{\"name\":\"Jaya\",\"color\":\"Red\",\"direction\":\"SW2\",\"C1\":\"Persistence/Winning Tool\",\"C2\":\"Annamaya Kosha\",\"C3\":\"Sex organs/Jananang\",\"C4\":\"Muladhar/Beta\"}'),
(43, 'Indra', '{\"p1\":\"Indra, the most important god in the Rig Veda is identified as the storm God or the Rain god. His thunderbolt Vajra and his bow Indradhanush protect mankind from the vagaries of nature, symbolized by the demons. Thus he is both revered as the God of rains and feared as the God of the storms. He represents the electrical energy brought to earth by the rain, rejuvenating it and making it fertile. He is sometimes seen as a fertility god.\",\"p2\":\"He is the ruler of the atmosphere and weathers are at his command. Inspite of his powerful arsenal of weapons, Indra, lord of the sky is a peaceful, heavenly ruler who offers refuge to all those who seek him and follow the path of Dharma. He is one of the powerful triad of Agni, Indra and Surya and is an important atmospheric or madhyam sthana deities. Indra was one of the twelve Adityas.\",\"p3\":\"Indra is the lord of the pada next to Jaya and positioned on the diagonal line connecting\"}', 'ॐरश्मिर्हरिकेशः पुरस्तात् सविताज्योतिरुदयाँ अजस्रम्।। तस्यपूषाप्रसवे यातिविद्वान् सम्पश्यन् ', 'assets/devtas/Indra S7S8.jpg', '{\"1\":\"Family stability, basic growth, thought process\",\"2\":\"It safeguards money, associated with conception, grounding.\",\"3\":\"A labour room is recommended here.\",\"4\":\"Pregnancy stabilizes with his powers only.\",\"5\":\"He gives strength, longevity and protection to life.\",\"6\":\"This place needs to be balance for safe delivery and to keep safe also.\",\"7\":\"Balance of Muladhar chakra comes from here\",\"8\":\"Imbalances gives challenges, instability and all the attributes of Muladhar Chakra get problematic.\",\"9\":\"Annamaya Kosha/Beta waves---day to day activities\"}', '{\"name\":\"Indra\",\"color\":\"blue\",\"direction\":\"SW1\",\"C1\":\"Nurturing/Protector\",\"C2\":\"Annamaya Kosha\",\"C3\":\"Right Shoulder/Dahina Skandh \",\"C4\":\"Muladhar/Beta\",\"C5\":\"Gomed\"}');
INSERT INTO `devtasdetails` (`id`, `name`, `description`, `sloka`, `image`, `points`, `otherDetails`) VALUES
(44, 'Sugriva', '{\"p1\":\"Though Sugriva literally means a slender neck, it refers to the God Hayagreeva or Hayasheersha (one having the face of a horse). The legend says that Hayasheersha knew the Madhu Vidya. Not considering him to be a worthwhile disciple, he refused to impart this skill to Lord Indra. He was threatened by Indra that if he taught this vidya to anyone, he would be beheaded. The Ashwini Kumars wanted to learn this Vidya. So they cut off his head and kept it safe. They then attached a horse\'s head, which was subsequently cut by Indra. Then the Ashwini Kumaras replaced the original head.\",\"p2\":\"This pada is good for studies and practice in the Vaastu Shastra and lies between South \"}', 'ॐसुषुम्णा: सूर्यरश्मिश्चन्द्रमांगधर्वस्तस्यनक्षत्राण्यप्सरसोभेकुरयो नाम। सनऽइदंब्रह्मक्षत्रंपातु तस्मैस्वाहा वाट्ताभ्यः स्वाहा।', 'assets/devtas/Sugriva W3.jpg', '{\"1\":\"Good grasping power\",\"2\":\"Who is capable of receiving beautifully and easily.\",\"3\":\"Receptive, receiving Power, Knowledge & Grasping Power, Retention& Saving\",\"4\":\"It makes us to receive as well as comprehend any subject.\",\"5\":\"One who can solve problems by merely listening to the problems\",\"6\":\"Power to memorise things\",\"7\":\"Best place to make Gym or Akhara, In Mahabharata times, Bheem, Duryodhna learned wrestling here.\",\"8\":\"Associated with communication and retention.\",\"9\":\"Washing Machine here responsible for forgetfulness and inability to remember things at the time of exams.\",\"10\":\"Kitchen here gives inability to present the knowledge they have gained.\",\"11\":\"Living /bedroom is associated with very good understanding and love for different subjects if balanced.\",\"12\":\"If extended, people keep on running to gather knowledge from different sources.\",\"13\":\"Red colour causes irritation towards newer ideas/subjects/domain of life\",\"14\":\"Village scene in black frames here gives buying a property becomes easy.\",\"15\":\"Entrance here gives money, growth and prosperity, also deeper understanding.\",\"16\":\"It ensures the process of receiving learning in the childhood and receiving money also when child grows up.\"}', '{\"name\":\"SUGREEV(W3)\",\"color\":\"Red\",\"direction\":\"WSW\",\"C1\":\"Receptive/Receiving Power\",\"C2\":\"Manomaya Kosha\",\"C3\":\"Left Calf/Banyi Pindli\",\"C4\":\"Vishuddhi/Alpha/\"}'),
(45, 'Savitra', '{\"p1\":\"Savitra is one of the 12 Adityas and is one of the most powerful energy areas of modern times. He was given importance in the Mahabharata period and thereafter considered as one of the important Adityas. In the Rig Veda, he is said to have controlled water and air. No one including Indra, Varuna and Mitra could break his laws. He follows a fixed set of rules and controls the sky.\",\"p2\":\"Intellectuals are divided in their opinion about Savitra. According to Yaska, Savitra period begins after the darkness ends. According to Sayana, the Sun before sunrise is Savitra and from sunrise to sunset is Sun.\",\"p3\":\"Savitra is the best medium for energy. When we move from the kendra padas of Brahma and move towards the south east corner, then we come across the pada for Savitra. The balance karmas of the previous birth can be analyzed from this section.\"}', 'ॐ उपयामगृहीतोसिसावित्रोसिचनोद्याश्च नोधाऽअसिचनोमयिधेहि। जिन्वयज्ञजिन्वयज्ञपतिंभगायदेवायत्वासवित्रे ॐभू भोः सावित्र इहा सवित्राय नमः।।', 'assets/devtas/Savitra S1S2.jpg', '{\"1\":\"Unlimited capabilities of resources.\",\"2\":\"It carries our activities to next level.\",\"3\":\"Savitra says, I am removing obstacles. Savitra says, move ahead.\",\"4\":\"Savitra is pranamaya kosha, mentally energize \",\"5\":\"Savitra is annamaya kosha, physically strength\",\"6\":\"It gives us the power of determination as well as power to enjoy luxuries.\",\"7\":\"This is the place where Gayatri mantra originates.\",\"8\":\"Shree Yantra is beneficial here\",\"9\":\"It brings you out of any problem with clear heart\"}', '{\"name\":\"SAVITRA\",\"color\":\"Red\",\"direction\":\"SE2\",\"C1\":\"Strength/Pusher\",\"C2\":\"Annamaya Kosha\",\"C3\":\"Palm/Hatheli\",\"C4\":\"Manipur/Beta\",\"C5\":\"Diamond/Cat’s Eye\"}');
